        conseils: "The Marseille — Martigues route follows one of Provence's most beautiful coastal roads. Weather permitting, ask your driver for the Côte Bleue road (D5) instead of the A55: it adds 15 minutes but the panorama over the Niolon, Méjean and Ensuès calanques is breathtaking. For Martigues sardinades (July-August, every Friday evening), arrive before 7pm to get a spot — a taxi is ideal as parking in old Martigues is virtually impossible on these evenings. The Miroir aux Oiseaux is most beautiful in early morning when canal waters are perfectly still. Martigues poutargue can be found at port fishmongers — expect €35-45 per piece for this exceptional product. For beaches, Carro and La Couronne (5 km south) offer fine sand and crystal-clear waters, less crowded than Marseille beaches. In winter, the mistral can blow very strongly over the Étang de Berre — our drivers know the conditions and adapt their speed.",
        comparaisonTransport: "Bus 34 (CarTreize network) connects Marseille (Joliette) to Martigues in about 1 hour for €2.50, but runs only every 30-45 minutes. There is no direct rail link Marseille — Martigues. By personal car, expect €5 in fuel with no tolls. The TaxiNeo taxi at €55 — €70 for 1 to 4 passengers offers speed (35 min vs 1h by bus), comfort (air conditioning, no multiple stops) and schedule flexibility. It is particularly advantageous in the evening and at weekends when bus frequency drops drastically.",
