        heroTitle: "Taxi Marseille — Aix TGV Station",
        heroSubtitle: "Fast connection to Aix-en-Provence TGV Station",
        description: "Taxi transfer from Marseille to Aix-en-Provence TGV Station on the Arbois plateau, for TGV connections to Paris and northern France.",
        routeDescription: "25 km — approximately 25 minutes via A7/A51",
        introduction: "Aix-en-Provence TGV Station is a strategic rail hub on the Mediterranean high-speed line, located on the Arbois plateau between Marseille and Aix-en-Provence. Opened in 2001, this futuristic station serves direct TGVs to Paris (3h), Lyon (1h20), Brussels and Lille. Paradoxically far from Aix's centre (15 km), it requires a road transfer. From Marseille, a taxi is often faster and more practical than going to Saint-Charles Station then taking a TER to Aix TGV. This transfer is particularly popular with business travellers and families with luggage.",
        itineraire: "From Marseille, take the A7 towards Lyon then switch to the A51 towards Aix-en-Provence. The 'Gare TGV Aix-en-Provence' exit is well signposted after the La Barque toll. The station sits on the Arbois plateau, somewhat isolated but well served by the motorway. Traffic flows well outside peak hours. The driver drops you directly in front of the departure hall, as close as possible to the platforms.",
