        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Marseille — Cavaillon costs around 14 euros and takes 1h to 1h20 with a frequent change at Avignon. There are few direct trains (2-3 per day). The Zou! bus costs 5 euros but takes 1h45 with stops at Salon-de-Provence and villages. By car, expect 11 euros in fuel and 7 euros in tolls, totalling 18 euros excluding parking. The TaxiNeo taxi at 95 to 125 euros offers direct door-to-door service. For 3-4 passengers (24 to 42 euros per person), it is the most practical solution for arriving with luggage and continuing to Luberon accommodation without using Cavaillon's outlying station.",
