        comparaisonTransport: "The train from Marseille to Sisteron takes about 2h30 to 3 hours with a change at Aix-en-Provence (TER Aix — Sisteron is infrequent, 4-5 trains per day). The ticket costs around 25 euros. There is no direct Marseille — Sisteron bus. By car, expect 20 euros in fuel and 12 euros in tolls, totalling 32 euros excluding parking. The TaxiNeo taxi at 195 to 245 euros offers a direct door-to-door transfer in 1h40. For 3-4 passengers (49 to 82 euros per person), it is faster and more comfortable than the train with connections, and especially suited to families with luggage heading to a holiday rental in Haute-Provence.",
