        conseils: "Menton's old town is best explored on foot: ask to be dropped at the port or the Promenade du Soleil. The exceptional gardens each require 1 to 2 hours — the Serre de la Madone garden (guided tours, €8) is the most remarkable. For the Lemon Festival (February), book your taxi 3-4 weeks ahead as the town is packed. The walk up to the Vieux-Château cemetery offers Menton's finest view over the bay and Italy — climb on foot from the church square. For an Italian excursion, Ventimiglia is 10 km away (famous Friday market for clothes and leather) and San Remo 40 km — your driver can take you there with a supplement. Restaurant Mirazur (3 Michelin stars, ranked world's best restaurant in 2019) is in Menton — booking essential several months ahead.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Marseille — Menton takes 2h45 to 3h30 (with change at Nice) for €25-40. The TGV (rare, via Nice) costs €40-85 and takes 3h. Flixbus offers the trip from €15 but takes at least 4h. By personal car, expect €28 in fuel and €20 in tolls, totalling €48 excluding parking. The TaxiNeo taxi at €290 — €360 (up to 4 passengers) offers complete door-to-door service. For 4 passengers, the per-person cost (€73 to €90) is comparable to train with connection, with the advantage of door-to-door service and flexibility — essential for enjoying this end-of-line destination.",
