        conseils: "Petrochemical zone workers appreciate our 24/7 service for shift transfers (3×8). Specify the exact industrial site when booking as the complex is extensive. For a swim in the lagoon, Champigny beach is the best-equipped with showers and a snack bar in summer. The old village is worth a stroll for the castle ruins and the view over the lagoon from the church esplanade. Berre market (Saturday morning, Place de la Résistance) is an authentic small-scale market. For birdwatchers, the southern lagoon shores between Berre and Saint-Chamas host flamingo colonies — walk at dawn or dusk for the best sightings. Old village restaurants serve brackish-water fish specialities, notably Étang de Berre eels.",
